{
  "texts": [
    "To include mustache toad in our cross-frog comparisons, we adopted the published annotation from ref.",
    "29 (Supplementary Note 3).",
    "We found 14,412 orthologous groups across the five genera with OrthoVenn2 64, including genes found in at least four of the five frog genera represented (Supplementary Fig. 4d).",
    "As expected, due to its reference-quality genome and well-studied transcriptome, only 72 of these clusters were not represented in X. tropicalis (and only 42 clusters from gene families present in six or more members among a larger set of seven frog species, see Supplementary Fig. 4e); the additional frog genomes each had between 575 and 712 of these genes missing (or mis-clustered), suggesting better than 95% completeness in the other species.",
    "For analyses of synteny, we further restricted our attention to 7292 one-to-one gene orthologs that were present on chromosomes (as opposed to unlinked scaffolds) in the \"core\" genomes X. tropicalis, H. boettgeri, E. coqui, E. pustulosus, and P. adspersus."
  ]
}